<br>
The bad things..<br>
<br>
  Like Balamur stated....Permanent Death...  This concept sounds alright, but the reality of it isn't good.  Sure, consequences of dying should be harsh..but comeon...  This will lead to an abundance of paranoid people...no one will trust anyone..Hey, look at that Uber-powerful warrior over there, I'm not going near him, cause I don't feel like losing the entire month I've spent on my guy.  And then, how about the Warrior?  Will that Warrior go explore an unknown dungeon, even with a group of friends?  Nay, six months is a long time wasted for a simple long fall into an area he can't escape.  ...hmm, Let's get a group of thirty Uber players to raid a high-level dungeon..umm, no thanks...in these cases, one death is too much...  Teamwork?  This will be out the window also, sacrificing yourself in EQ so your party can escape is surely the height of bravery...this will never happen in Dawn though...I don't think someone would do this for the good of the group in the same situation..it's going to be all about looking out for number one.  Resurrection is apparently possible, however it has a high price, the sacrifice of an equal or higher level person than the one being resurrected.<br>
<br>
  Extinction -  Apparently, the designers will allow races to become extinct...in other words, Kill all the Ogres in the game, and no other Ogres will be able to be generated(because of the Birth concept implemented).  People are people, and the majority of people will prefer one race over another...I can see as time goes on, one race dominating all others, until there are only that race running around...imagine a world full of Sylvans...not a good thing, (Nothing against you Sylvan players lol) diversity-wise.<br>
<br>
  Inprisonment - Apparently, you can knock someone uncouncious, then drag their body to a prison...this is a bad thing in my opinion...this ruins someones gameplay...Imagine a group of evil teenagers all Uber-level terrorizing innocents, dragging them to prison, effectively ruining their night of gameplay...sitting around in a cell isn't my idea of a fun night online.<br>
<br>
Some good things however.....<br>
<br>
  Building...it sounds like Trade Skills will be very fun in this game....don't like the new Sword you just got from a baddie?  Instead of selling it to a vendor for some chump change, melt it down and make another one....or...melt it down for materials to make your new Castle!  Apparently you can, for example, make a stone block, put it down...it's now part of the world...make a bunch of stone blocks, make them in to the shape of a room, add some chairs...congrats, you just made yourself a Throne Room. =)  Of course, you can also make a Catapult to knock down that throne room..  I can see some wonderful things here...a group of like minded players works together in a night, and builds an epic-sized castle...then declares themselves rulers of that area, summarily imprisoning people that don't pay them tribute.....the call goes out, and a neighboring kingdom comes the liberate the area with seige weapons and glorious battle to ensue.  <br>
<br>
  Experience - They say you can gain experience from doing Trade skills, baking, smithing..etc...  Theoretically, you could become Uber-level without lifting a sword... =)  Gwion, I think you'll like that idea, since I remember you expressing your disdain at having to kill things in EQ to level.  However, in a game where if you die, that is final, I think having a 50th level Baker that you've spent six months working on die, all because you can't block a sword swing sounds like an awful shame to me.<br>
<br>
  All in all, from reading all I could about this game, I get the impression that these are people not satisfied with EQ and the like sort of games, and believe they can make a game that is better.  I hope they succeed!  LOL..if this games turns out to be as good as it sounds, I can surely see EQ losing this Druid as a player, at least, until my character in Dawn dies. =\ <p><b>
