<br>
Some other interestings you didn't mention were pets and followers.<br>
<br>
A follower is any creature given, sold, or stolen by yourself that is above 1st level already. Interestingly, you can train certain animals and then sell them (horses for example). It would be your follower until you sold it, and then you would change it over to the new person.<br>
<br>
Pets are a different matter entirely. If you find a creature that is 1st level (difficult because they mature and level much as players do), you can claim it as a pet. It would be untrained and more than a bit unruly, but it would be yours and basically do what you told it (probably also after some training). It will guard you at all times, even when you were sleeping.<br>
<br>
NOW then... is it just me, or do I sense a nice opportunity to have my own pack of wolves? A friendly dragon or two?<br>
<br>
